dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile represents forest types in Kenya. These data were acquired from FAO's Africover dataset (2000). This layer includes data for natural and seminatural forested landscapes such as closed canopy forests and other forest types with more open crown cover.This data was used in Map 1.3 and Map 7.1 in Nature's Benefits in Kenya: An Atlas of Ecosystems and Human Well-Being.
dc_publisher_s: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
